  (text_box "Description: Clean +5 V Analog LDO. Low-noise LDO (U9, ADP7142, fixed 5.0 V) post-regulating the +5 V analog rail. It takes the TPS63802 buck-boost's raw output (TPS63802_VOUT, set to ~5.5 V) and scrubs the switching ripple to produce a quiet +5 V for the op-amp positive supply and the LM27761 negative-rail generator. C23 is the input cap, C24 the output cap, and C25 (on SS) sets the soft-start ramp."
    (at 222.25 25.4 0) (size 58.42 17.78)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid 029c4ace-1007-4c96-b97e-b5b643cd2e61)
  )
  (text_box "Description: −5 V Analog Rail (inverting LDO charge pump). Regulated negative-supply generator (U7, LM27761) producing a clean −5 V (LM27761_VOUT) from the +5 V rail, for the negative op-amp supply in the analog front end. The device inverts +5 V with an internal switched-capacitor charge pump (flying cap C15 on C+/C−) and regulates/cleans the result with its built-in LDO. C16 is the input cap, C17 the output cap, and R19/R20 set the regulated output magnitude via the VFB divider. EN is tied to VIN (always on)."
    (at 133.35 25.4 0) (size 83.82 15.24)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid 7f75d339-48a3-4269-9488-84dc34cf02e9)
  )
  (text_box "Description: 3.0 V Precision Reference. Voltage reference (U8, REF3030) providing a stable, accurate +3V0 rail used as the ADC reference for the acquisition front end. Powered from +3V3 with bypass cap C21; the precision 3.0 V output defines the ADC's full-scale span independently of the noisy supply rails, so measured voltages stay accurate."
    (at 133.35 83.82 0) (size 83.82 12.7)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid 93b11782-2887-40ae-b487-c28366a00538)
  )
  (text_box "Description: +5.5 V Buck-Boost (pre-regulator). Buck-boost regulator (U6, TPS63802) generating a 5.5 V intermediate rail from BQ24075_OUT. Because OUT swings 3.0-4.8 V - straddling the target - a buck-boost is used so it regulates cleanly whether the input is below or near the output. The 5.5 V output feeds the ADP7142 LDO, which cleans it down to the final +5 V analog rail (op-amp positive supply and the −5 V charge-pump stage); the extra 0.5 V gives the LDO its dropout headroom. Inductor L4 bridges the L1/L2 switch nodes; R21/R22 set the 5.5 V output via the FB divider (R21 = 910 k, R22 = 91 k); R23 enables the device; C18/C19 provide input/output decoupling."
    (at 16.51 83.82 0) (size 111.76 15.24)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid 9f9e01ea-5859-4056-ae10-e050a94af698)
  )
  (text_box "Description: 3.3 V Digital Rail (buck-boost). Single-inductor buck-boost regulator (U5, TPS63802) producing the main +3V3 logic supply from the charger's BQ24075_OUT rail. Because OUT swings from ~4.7 V (charging) down to ~3.0 V (low battery), a buck-boost is used so the output stays regulated whether the input is above or below 3.3 V. The external inductor (L2) bridges the L1/L2 switch nodes; R16/R17 set the output via the FB divider; R18 enables the device; C13/C14 provide input/output decoupling.\n"
    (at 16.51 25.4 0) (size 111.76 12.7)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid b65207d1-c88a-47ee-bf39-d36ce3961674)
  )

  (text "Regulation / Rails" (at 13.97 20.32 0)
